    "notes": "Running the game as a Flatpak on Alpine Linux edge.\n\nGame could be installed with no issues. Launching the game works as well. The login screen pops up on Wayland but is white; the content is only shown when started through X11. Even on X11 logging in takes a few tries to complete, with each new screen first showing, then being full white again, with the solution being to close the login screen and trying a few times.\n\nThe menu loads, but joining a game doesn't work. Joining a lobby gives the following error:\n\n---\n\nThere is a missing or corrupt data file that is required for the game to run.\n\n[...]\n\nData file:\n../../../Athena/Content/Paks/Core_3a5af39e-5650-452b-9606-5199b34d8318-WindowsClient_P101.pak\nReferencer: N/A\nError code: P06\n\n---\n\nThe file exists on the filesystem, at least, so it might be corrupt. Verifying the integrity of game files through Steam doesn't fix this, and doing it in the game through the pop-up after it crashed also doesn't fix it (and crashes the game after running for around 5 minutes, too). The game is essentially stuck in a verify, start, crash loop and is thus unplayable.",
